Common.Strapline.Common.Text: A Top Shelf Kent Town Opportunity

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
For Sale via Public Auction Thursday 26th August 2021

CBRE Metropolitan Investments are very excited to be appointed exclusively to handle the sale of this sensational Kent Town opportunity that truly offers something to each buyer profile. The property is configured as three separate units offering a mixture of showroom and office space and is offered to market fully leased.

The precinct of Kent Town has undergone significant gentrification since the rezoning to Urban Corridor allowing for high-density development increasing residential population. Additionally, given the close proximity to the CBD it has become a highly desired spot for businesses to set up their homes due to strong growth forecast in land values and ever-increasing amenity.

We further highlight the below key features of 68 King William Street for consideration:
-   Land area of 953sqm* 
-   Dual access via King William Street and Little Rundle Street
-   Zoned Urban Corridor (Business) allowing for development up to five (5) levels (STCC)
-   Three tenancies totaling 621sqm all offering rear access and currently fully leased
-   8 on-site car parks
-   Owner occupier potential through redevelopment
-   Passing income of $89,152pa*
